    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-16T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-16T04:00:00-05:00" n="910"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d910">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/812: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-16T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 16, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1302. Supplementing my 1295, December 15, I urge that no time be lost in
                    returning Liberator to Eskisehir. If plane is returned immediately and the
                    secret of its departure with 8 of internees continues to be kept it is by no
                    means impossible that the Turkish military authorities may put no obstacles in
                    the way of a repeat performance.</p>
                <p>Any reply to my 1295 or to this telegram should be marked to be decoded only by
                    the Ambassador.</p>
                <p>Please inform General Arnold of the foregoing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
